# Azumi License

Copyright (c) 2024 Dracon

## Summary

Azumi is **free for individuals and small teams**. Companies with 5 or more
employees must purchase a commercial license.

---

## License Terms

### 1. Free Use

You may use, copy, modify, and distribute this software **at no cost** if:

- You are an individual using it for personal projects
- You are using it for open source projects
- You are a company or organization with **fewer than 5 employees**
- You are evaluating the software for potential purchase

### 2. Commercial License Required

A commercial license is required if:

- You are a company or organization with **5 or more employees**
- You are using Azumi to build production applications

### 3. Commercial License Pricing

| Company Size       | Annual License |
| ------------------ | -------------- |
| 5-25 employees     | $2,000/year    |
| 26-100 employees   | $6,000/year    |
| 101-500 employees  | $12,000/year   |
| 500+ employees     | $25,000/year   |

Purchase at: **https://dracon.uk/azumi/license**

For questions: license@dracon.uk

### 4. What You Get

- Legal permission to use Azumi in your organization
- All features included (no "enterprise" restrictions)
- License is per-organization, not per-seat
- Build unlimited applications

### 5. What This Is NOT

- This is not a SaaS subscription (no cloud services included)
- This is not a support contract (community support via Discord)
- This is not a warranty (software provided as-is)

---

## Additional Terms

### Definitions

- **"Employee"** includes full-time, part-time, and contract workers who work
  for the organization regularly.
- **"Organization"** means the legal entity (company, LLC, etc.) using the
  software, including all subsidiaries and affiliates.

### Enforcement

Violation of this license may result in legal action. If you are unsure whether
your use requires a commercial license, please contact us.

### Updates

This license applies to all versions of Azumi. Future versions may have
different terms, but your license covers the version you purchased for.

